oakcurric:unit-3494
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "On se prépare aux examens"@en ;
  curric:slug "on-prepare-aux-examens" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit draws together known grammar and vocabulary in practising the skills for
  the different elements of the GCSE examination."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this final unit, pupils apply their knowledge in extended spoken
  production, transcription, listening, reading and responding to longer passages, and extended
  written production. Pupils will also be able to ask and answer questions in role play, photo
  card and conversation practice.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-3494-6 ;
  curric:id "3494"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.091629Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2872
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: mon nouveau pays"@en ;
  curric:slug "my-neighbourhood-mon-nouveau-pays" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit examines the use of direct and indirect object pronouns in the past
  tense, infinitives used as nouns, and the perfect tense when used as the equivalent of the
  present perfect. Furthermore, pupils will meet the present tense with depuis, être en
  train de, and venir de + infinitive."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Having previously met both the perfect tense and direct and indirect
  object pronouns, pupils will now combine these skills in this unit.They will meet texts
  focusing on contemporary contexts such as immigration and environmental issues and will
  respond by completing extended, scaffolded writing using prior knowledge as well as new,
  higher level structures. Pupils learn to communicate about real, topical matters of global
  importance using a range of tenses and grammatical structures which will be useful in a
  variety of future KS4 themes.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2872-7 ;
  curric:id "2872"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.460743Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2883
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Lifestyle and wellbeing/Travel and tourism: la culture francophone"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-communication-and-the-world-around-us-la-culture-francophone" ;
  rdfs:comment """This cultural unit consolidates present tense regular verb patterns, adjectives
  and adverbs, possessive adjectives and a range of pronouns. In addition it further
  develops the imperative, including the nous form for 'let's + verb', and teaches the two
  uses of present participles."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit focuses on new knowledge of Francophone culture, exploring the
  city of Montréal, cultural diversity in Morocco, Francophone sports teams, art, and
  government. Grammatically this unit revisits much from KS3 and earlier in KS4, but also
  challenges pupils with the introduction of present participles and further imperative and
  word pattern rules. Pupils learn to describe, but also to express opinions on, a range of
  cultural and political topics, and further develop key skills essential at KS4 such as
  reading and responding to texts, describing photos, translation and extended writing.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-7 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2883-8 ;
  curric:id "2883"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.469259Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2868
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My personal world: Mes intérêts"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-mes-interets" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits subject pronouns, -er and -re verbs in the present tense, and
  two-verb constructions with 'aimer' in the context of describing free time activities. It
  also consolidates silent final letters, and the sound-symbol correspondences [-er,-ez,-é],
  [on], [en,an] and hard [s]."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils secure and expand their understanding of present tense
  regular -er and -re verbs in all persons.This is gateway knowledge which they have covered in
  KS3 and need to master for KS4, where conjugating verbs competently is key to communicating
  effectively. Pupils will expand their personal repertoire of verbs, and learn to identify
  different categories of -re verbs, in order to be able to work more independently. Pupils
  will also build on their knowledge of some common sound-symbol correspondences, beginning to
  apply these more consistently and also identifying exceptions.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2868-6 ;
  curric:id "2868"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.510700Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2875
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: Ma carrière"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-ma-carriere" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit consolidates modal verbs in the present tense and introduces the
  conditional with vouloir in the context of career plans. There is also an extensive focus
  on word pattern rules, introducing new rules for the formation of adverbs from adjectives
  and adding in- or im- to mean 'opposite of'."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on their knowledge of modal verbs from KS3, pupils will develop
  mastery of these in all persons of the verb in the present tense and they will also learn how
  to express future wishes and plans using the conditional with vouloir. Set in the context of
  the world of work, pupils will listen to and read texts which explore different career
  pathways, discuss the pros and cons of different jobs, and articulate their own desires for
  the future. Further units at KS4 will consolidate the thematic vocabulary and allow further
  practice of these structures.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2875-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2875-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2875-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2875-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2875-5 ;
  curric:id "2875"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.552902Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-derivational-word-patterns ,
    oakcurric:thread-ask-and-answer-spoken-questions ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2876
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Studying and my future: Au boulot"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-au-boulot" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit pupils apply prior knowledge of irregular verbs, question-forming
  with question words, indefinite adjectives, interrogative adjectives and demonstrative
  adjectives. They will also deepen their understanding of relative clauses and learn how to
  form the imperative."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Building on grammatical knowledge from KS3 and thematic knowledge from
  previous units at KS4, pupils use questions and answers in the present and the perfect tense
  to communicate about work situations. The addition of relative clauses enables pupils to form
  longer, more complex sentences. The focus on the imperative, which is new learning, will
  allow pupils to practise talking in both formal and informal situations, differentiating
  between talking to colleagues or other adults and their friends. This understanding of formal
  and informal language is a key skill to develop going forward at KS4.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2876-6 ;
  curric:id "2876"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.675817Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-listen-and-respond-to-longer-passages ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2870
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: visites et rendez-vous"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-visites-et-rendez-vous" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit further explores the use of direct object pronouns and introduces pupils
  to indirect object pronouns and their pre-verbal positioning, within the context of
  cultural visits and social gatherings. In addition, there is a focus on the pronunciation
  of hard and soft consonants."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will have already met pronouns which precede the verb, and this
  unit builds on this knowledge, with a specific focus on the correct positioning of indirect
  object pronouns. They will be exposed to this new knowledge in both culturally rich and
  everyday social settings. Pupils learn to recognise when and why direct or indirect object
  pronouns are used in a range of text types before moving on to translation, and finally
  aiming to employ these accurately, using correct word order, as they adopt this new language
  into their productive repertoire.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2870-6 ;
  curric:id "2870"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.681011Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2873
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: Ma famille"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-ma-famille" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit revisits definite, indefinite and partitive articles, possessive
  adjectives, as well as adjective agreement and positioning rules. Pupils will learn one
  further adjective agreement rule. Lessons also further practise liaison and silent final
  letters."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """Pupils will build on their already sound KS3 knowledge of adjectives
  across this unit, ensuring accuracy in both word order and gender and number agreements. Also
  refocusing on the use of articles and possessive adjectives, this unit enables pupils to
  apply the new adjectival rules alongside familiar language and in familiar contexts, talking
  about family relationships. This unit prepares pupils for following units which will focus on
  comparative and superlative use of these adjectives.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2873-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2873-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2873-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2873-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2873-5 ;
  curric:id "2873"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.683737Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners ,
    oakcurric:thread-adjectives ,
    oakcurric:thread-word-order ,
    oakcurric:thread-read-and-respond-to-texts ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2877
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "My personal world: Mes amis"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-mes-amis" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit introduces verbs that follow the pattern of connaître in the present and
  perfect tense and extends pupils' use of impersonal verbs. It also develops mastery of the
  imperfect tense of regular verbs, set in the context of past and present friendships and
  activities."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils will return to a familiar context, focusing on
  friendships and making free time plans, whilst deepening their grasp of higher level
  structures such as impersonal verbs, learning a new verb pattern in the present tense, and
  expanding their knowledge of the imperfect tense. This will enable them to make contrasts
  between their lives when they were younger and today, and to talk about what they were doing
  when something happened. Being able to confidently switch between tenses is a key skill to be
  developed further at KS4 and beyond.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2877-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2877-2 ,
