oakcurric:unit-2888
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "People and lifestyle: Révisions: Les études"@en ;
  curric:slug "people-and-lifestyle-revisions-les-etudes" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit continues to revisit known grammar and vocabulary from the course, this
  time focusing on future and conditional verb formation alongside the present tense. In
  addition it secures knowledge of verbs followed by infinitives, infinitives used as nouns,
  and a range of prepositions."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils revise previous grammar and vocabulary knowledge in
  the context of their future study and life at university. This unit draws together the future
  tense, the conditional and the present tense. They practise applying more complex language,
  including verbs, nouns and prepositions with greater confidence and fluency.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2888-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2888-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2888-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2888-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2888-5 ;
  curric:id "2888"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.794110Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-future-and-conditional .

oakcurric:unit-2880
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Media and technology: les médias"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-les-medias" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit expands topic-specific vocabulary on a range of media topics, including
  TV and cinema, computer technology and social networks. It further develops pupil
  knowledge of negation, revisiting previously met negative structures and introducing
  ne...ni...ni... with all tenses."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit develops ability to communicate about topics related to popular
  culture, media, and technology. Pupils will use a range of new vocabulary and consolidate
  already known grammar as they discuss topics which form part of everyday lives in modern
  society. The use of negative structures, following on from previous units focusing on these,
  will enable pupils to discuss the limitations and risks, as well as the benefits, of social
  media, computers, and celebrity culture. These structures can be applied to all future KS4
  topics where there is an element of opinion and debate.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2880-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2880-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2880-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2880-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2880-5 ;
  curric:id "2880"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:23.857841Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
