oakcurric:unit-2886
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: Un film francophone"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-un-film-francophone" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on consolidating the present tense and past participles of
  regular verbs and examines the use of the passive voice in the context of a Francophone
  film."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit pupils will develop their film vocabulary knowledge beyond
  media topics covered at KS3 and earlier in KS4, learning to describe themes, action and
  characters and build up to writing a review of a film. To this end they will further secure
  their knowledge of present and past tense regular verbs and will also begin to explore the
  use of the passive voice. Both the theme and grammar of this unit are good preparation for
  future learning beyond KS4 for those students keen to continue in their language learning.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2886-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2886-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2886-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2886-4 ;
  curric:id "2886"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.123801Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-cultural-spotlight ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-extend-written-and-spoken-production .

oakcurric:unit-2887
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Communication and the world around us: Révisions: la vie en francophonie"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-revisions-la-vie-en-francophonie" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit begins formal revision, with known grammar and vocabulary reactivated
  throughout. Pupils apply knowledge of regular and irregular verbs in the present, perfect
  and imperfect tenses, reflexive verbs, feminine and plural noun formations as well as
  revisiting articles and pronouns."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """In this unit, pupils revise previous grammar and vocabulary knowledge in
  the contexts of the life of a Francophone teenager, a cultural visit to Cannes, and the
  history of Quebec. As pupils' knowledge has progressed, this unit draws together past and
  present tenses, including reflexive verbs. Pupils also revisit different categories of
  articles, pronouns, and rules for noun formation. They practise applying more complex
  language with greater confidence and fluency, whilst further developing their Francophone
  cultural knowledge.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2887-7 ;
  curric:id "2887"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:24.171861Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
  curric:isUnitOf
    oakcurric:scheme-languages-key-stage-4 ;
  curric:includesThread
    oakcurric:thread-the-present ,
    oakcurric:thread-the-past ,
    oakcurric:thread-nouns-and-determiners .

oakcurric:unit-2869
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Travel and tourism: La France est belle!"@en ;
  curric:slug "communication-and-the-world-around-us-la-france-est-belle" ;
  rdfs:comment """In this unit, pupils re-examine verbs like choisir, partir and venir in the
  present, and add to this verbs like ouvrir. They revisit questions, pre-nominal
  adjectives, contraction of articles after à and de, and expand knowledge of negation. A
  further focus is the use of direct object pronouns."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit builds on pupils' prior understanding of -ir verb patterns,
  question-forming and verbal negation by first recapping familiar language before adding in
  new verbs and negative structures. Pupils use their prior and new knowledge to build
  questions and positive and negative statements to communicate in a culturally rich context,
  discovering many of France's famous attractions. Direct object pronouns, touched on at KS3,
  are also consolidated and expanded to cover all persons in new contexts, preparing pupils for
  further work on the preverbal position of a range of pronouns at KS4.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2869-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2869-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2869-3 ,
