oakcurric:unit-2885
  a curric:Unit ;
  rdfs:label "Popular culture: La vie quotidienne"@en ;
  curric:slug "popular-culture-la-vie-quotidienne" ;
  rdfs:comment """This unit focuses on mastering the use of reflexive pronouns and verbs. It also
  revisits perfect and imperfect tenses, relative clauses and negation, and introduces the
  past participles of modal verbs. There is a further focus on avant de + infinitive and
  après avoir + past participle."""@en ;
  curric:whyThisWhyNow """This unit explores a range of everyday contexts which allow pupils to
  deepen understanding of a range of grammar points met at KS3 and KS4. Reflexive and modal
  verbs feature particularly strongly in describing daily routine, household chores and
  preparing for exams. Daily routine is covered through the life of a Francophone band, so
  pupils also gain popular cultural knowledge and learn to talk about others as well as
  themselves. Pupils also expand their transactional vocabulary in practical everyday contexts
  such as shopping trips, preparing them both for role-play and real life scenarios.""" ;
  curric:hasPriorKnowledgeRequirement
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-1 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-2 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-3 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-4 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-5 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-6 ,
    oakcurric:priorknowledge-2885-7 ;
  curric:id "2885"^^xsd:positiveInteger;
  dcterms:modified "2026-06-07T15:29:26.176744Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
